         <ref id="fn1">
            <label>1.</label>
            <mixed-citation publication-type="other">These approaches lack a single name in the literature, where one finds terms such as “interpretive”, “postpositivist”, “pragmatic”, “critical”, and so forth applied to them. For example, the annual conference for researchers in this field is called the Interpretative Policy Analysis Conference. And yet the journal associated with the conference is titled<italic>Critical Policy Studies</italic>. We have opted for the term “discursive approach”, which enabled us to adopt a wider scope and to better differentiate between the various methods that we shall mention below, in particular the “interpretive” and “critical” approaches.</mixed-citation>
         </ref>
